comments: White (BOS) and Siakam (IND) make incidental contact with each other as they meet in the air reaching for the rebound.
Holiday (BOS) is moving alongside Nesmith's (IND) path and marginal body contact occurs during Nesmith's drive to the basket.
Brown (BOS) jumps alongside Hield (IND) and marginal body contact occurs during Hield's layup attempt.
Hield (IND) makes clean contact with the ball.
Holiday (BOS) does not establish the ball in the frontcourt within eight seconds.
White (BOS) briefly places his hand to Nembhard's (IND) front and quickly slides it off before contesting his driving shot attempt.
Tatum (BOS) establishes himself in Turner's (IND) path and the two players briefly engage and disengage.
Porzingis (BOS) briefly has a hand on Nesmith's (IND) shoulder and releases as he pursues the rebound.
Turner (IND) briefly engages with Tatum (BOS) in the lane.
Hield (IND) cleanly dislodges the ball from Porzingis (BOS).
White (BOS) commits a take foul on Hield (IND). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
Turner (IND) does not give a step of distance when establishing himself in a screening position behind Holiday (BOS) and delivering contact.
Holiday (BOS) is moving alongside Nembhard's (IND) path and marginal body contact before Holiday makes clean contact with the ball.
White (BOS) legally contests Nesmith's (IND) jump shot attempt and makes clean contact with the ball.
Tatum (BOS) and Turner (IND) briefly engage and disengage in the lane.
White (BOS) is the last player to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds.
Tatum (BOS) makes clean contact with the ball blocking the shot attempt by Turner (IND) and any ensuing contact is incidental.
Hield (IND) grasps and quickly releases White's (BOS) jersey during the throw-in.
The shot clock expires before Boston gains possession of the ball.
Turner (IND) commits a take foul on Holiday (BOS).
Toppin (IND) briefly places his right hand on Tatum's (BOS) right arm as he prepares to elevate for the jump ball, but immediately removes it.

Replay review of the foul called on Tatum (BOS) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed successful.  Tatum makes clean contact with the ball to block Nesmith's (IND) shot attempt and any contact with his arm is marginal.  The ball is loose at the time of the whistle and play resumes with a jump ball at center circle.
Siakam (IND) deflects the loose ball out of bounds.
Tatum (BOS) briefly engages with Siakam (IND) and releases to receive the throw-in.
